cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on learning sentence embeddings with syntactic structure and evaluating their quality. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses methods for learning embeddings and evaluates their performance. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with natural language processing and representation learning. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses neural network models for learning sentence embeddings. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the least likely category, but still possible as the paper may discuss applications of sentence embeddings in image captioning or other visual tasks.
